  <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\to  B]]></fr:tex> be a local homomorphism (N.B. all rings are now Noetherian), and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {m}]]></fr:tex> be the maximal ideal of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.
    Then the following conditions are equivalent:</fr:p>
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;i. &quot;">
      <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B/\mathfrak {m}B]]></fr:tex> is of finite dimension over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k=A/\mathfrak {m}]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>

    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;ii. &quot;">
      <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {m}B]]></fr:tex> is an ideal of definition, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B/\mathfrak {r}(B)=k(B)]]></fr:tex> is an extension of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k=k(A)]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>

    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;iii. &quot;">
      The completion <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\widehat {B}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is finite over the completion <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\widehat {A}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>

  </html:ol>
</fr:mainmatter>
